BT /F2 16 Tf 72.0 720.0 Td (Purchase Requisition Approval Policy) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 72.0 692.0 Td (Document ID: POL-PROC-001   |   Type: POLICY   |   Effective: 2024-01-01) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 662.0 Td (PURCHASE REQUISITION APPROVAL POLICY) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 646.0 Td (Document ID: POL-PROC-001) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 630.0 Td (Version: 3.1) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 614.0 Td (Effective Date: 2024-01-01) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 598.0 Td (Owner: Chief Procurement Officer) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 574.0 Td (1. PURPOSE) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 558.0 Td (This policy defines the approval thresholds and routing rules for all purchase) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 542.0 Td (requisitions \(PRs\) raised through the supply chain management system. It applies) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 526.0 Td (to all procurement of materials, components, and indirect goods.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 502.0 Td (2. APPROVAL THRESHOLDS) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 478.0 Td (2.1 Auto-Approval \(Preferred Vendor\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 462.0 Td (Purchase requisitions with an estimated cost below $5,000 submitted against a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 446.0 Td (preferred vendor are pre-approved and require no further review. The system may) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 430.0 Td (proceed to issue a purchase order automatically.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 406.0 Td (2.2 Manager Approval \($5,000 \20023 $25,000\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 390.0 Td (Purchase requisitions with an estimated cost between $5,000 and $25,000) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 374.0 Td (\(inclusive\) require manager approval before a purchase order is issued. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 358.0 Td (procurement system must route the requisition to the responsible manager and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 342.0 Td (suspend processing until a decision is recorded.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 318.0 Td (2.3 Executive Approval \(Above $25,000\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 302.0 Td (Purchase requisitions with an estimated cost exceeding $25,000 must follow the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 286.0 Td (executive approval process and cannot be processed through the automated) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 270.0 Td (procurement workflow. Such requisitions are denied by the system and must be re-) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 254.0 Td (submitted through the Capital Expenditure \(CapEx\) review board.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 230.0 Td (3. VENDOR CONSTRAINTS) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 206.0 Td (3.1 Preferred Vendor Requirement) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 190.0 Td (For standard catalogue materials \(urgency level: low or medium\), procurement must) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 174.0 Td (use a preferred vendor. Purchase requisitions below $5,000 using a non-preferred) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 158.0 Td (vendor require manager approval even if they would otherwise be auto-approved.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 134.0 Td (3.2 Forbidden Vendors) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 118.0 Td (Vendors placed on the Restricted Vendor List \(RVL\) are forbidden from receiving) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 102.0 Td (purchase orders. Any requisition naming an RVL vendor must be denied immediately) Tj ET
endstream
