stream
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 720.0 Td (regardless of amount.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 696.0 Td (4. URGENCY OVERRIDES) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 672.0 Td (4.1 Critical Urgency) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 656.0 Td (Requisitions classified as critical urgency \(on-hand stock is more than twice) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 640.0 Td (below safety stock level\) may be escalated to manager approval regardless of) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 624.0 Td (amount, bypassing the standard auto-approval threshold. The manager must respond) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 608.0 Td (within 4 business hours.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 584.0 Td (4.2 High Urgency) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 568.0 Td (Requisitions classified as high urgency follow standard thresholds but are) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 552.0 Td (flagged for expedited review.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 528.0 Td (5. AUDIT REQUIREMENTS) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 512.0 Td (Every approval decision \20024 auto-approved, manager-approved, or denied \20024 must be) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 496.0 Td (recorded with the rule that triggered it, the requisition amount, and the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 480.0 Td (applicable threshold. This record constitutes the audit artifact for compliance) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 464.0 Td (purposes.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 440.0 Td (6. POLICY REVIEW) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 424.0 Td (This policy is reviewed annually by the Chief Procurement Officer and updated as) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 408.0 Td (business conditions change. The current version supersedes all prior versions.) Tj ET
endstream
